modules.description: This module implements a monadic API client for HTTP operations using the `io` type to sequence asynchronous calls. It provides `get`, `post`, `put`, and `delete` functions to send requests with custom headers and URLs, returning responses as strings within the `io` monad. It supports composing HTTP interactions with monadic utilities like `map`, `bind`, and `fail` to handle success and error cases directly in the `io` context.
